article.headline: Indiana St. 57, Green Bay 56
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Jordan Printy's 3-pointer with 15 seconds left boosted Indiana State to a 57-56 victory over Green Bay on Monday night. Printy led his team with 12 points, all on 3-pointers, as the Sycamores started 4-0 for the first time since 2005-06. Myles Walker and R.J. Mahurin added 10 points apiece, and Dwayne Lathan had a game-best seven rebounds. Steve Baker scored 15 points to lead the Phoenix (2-3). Terry Johnson added 12 and Brennan Cougill 10. For the first time this season, Green Bay was outrebounded as the Sycamores controlled the boards 35-31. Back-to-back 3-pointers by Steve Baker pushed Green Bay ahead 54-50 with 5:07 to go, and Johnson's layup made it 56-52 with 2:32 left. But Steve McWhorter trimmed it to 56-54 with 1:58 to play, and neither team scored again until Printy won it.
